WEBVTT

1
00:00:17.310 --> 00:00:21.618
In my career. I've helped
make sequencing of human

2
00:00:21.660 --> 00:00:25.428
and other genomes.
all your genes. possible.

3
00:00:25.470 --> 00:00:26.448
and then affordable.

4
00:00:26.490 --> 00:00:30.273
so bringing it down
from $3 billion to $300.

5
00:00:31.350 --> 00:00:34.308
We've also been involved
in writing and editing DNA.

6
00:00:34.350 --> 00:00:37.668
which involves being able to
synthesize DNA from scratch

7
00:00:37.710 --> 00:00:41.313
and also to make tiny edits
with enzymes like CRISPR.

8
00:00:42.720 --> 00:00:45.408
I probably should have
no opinion being. you know.

9
00:00:45.450 --> 00:00:48.708
a scientist that's open to possibilities.

10
00:00:48.750 --> 00:00:49.541
To some extent.

11
00:00:49.583 --> 00:00:51.788
the entire universe has
some kind of intelligence to it.

12
00:00:51.830 --> 00:00:56.830
It just has this amazing
computational ability.

13
00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:00.168
Yeah. I think we haven't even
scratched the surface even

14
00:01:00.210 --> 00:01:05.210
in all science fiction of
what aliens could be like.

15
00:01:05.880 --> 00:01:07.458
It's exciting. the possibility

16
00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:10.818
that we are not only seeing aliens.

17
00:01:10.860 --> 00:01:12.757
but having close encounters with 'em.

18
00:01:22.985 --> 00:01:24.498
Were you
visited by aliens as well?

19
00:01:24.540 --> 00:01:27.086
Yeah. and I had a UFO experience.

20
00:01:27.128 --> 00:01:29.625
That was in '67. '68.

21
00:01:29.667 --> 00:01:31.308
And you
weren't high or anything?

22
00:01:31.350 --> 00:01:32.388
No. I didn't do drugs.

23
00:01:32.430 --> 00:01:33.528
I didn't even drink back then.

24
00:01:33.570 --> 00:01:35.868
- And who visited?
- They just randomly picked me

25
00:01:35.910 --> 00:01:38.568
and I woke up while they were doing it.

26
00:01:38.610 --> 00:01:39.798
I'm going. "What the fuck's going on?"

27
00:01:39.840 --> 00:01:41.313
My room was white.

28
00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:46.638
We're talking today

29
00:01:46.680 --> 00:01:49.068
with Harvard University
psychiatrist John Mack.

30
00:01:49.110 --> 00:01:52.368
who studied the cases of
about a hundred people at least

31
00:01:52.410 --> 00:01:54.528
who claimed that they'd
been abducted by aliens.

32
00:01:54.570 --> 00:01:56.718
One of Dr. Mack's patients. Randy here.

33
00:01:56.760 --> 00:01:59.283
says his abduction
occurred while he was awake.

34
00:02:04.890 --> 00:02:07.548
What do you remember from that moment on?

35
00:02:07.590 --> 00:02:11.328
When I regained
consciousness. it wasn't real quick.

36
00:02:11.370 --> 00:02:12.601
I didn't know where I was.

37
00:02:12.643 --> 00:02:14.328
I felt like I was dying.

38
00:02:14.370 --> 00:02:18.828
And this is what really fueled the panic

39
00:02:18.870 --> 00:02:21.070
when I finally laid
eyes on these creatures.

40
00:02:35.790 --> 00:02:40.398
They seem to cut across
every socioeconomic level.

41
00:02:40.440 --> 00:02:41.388
They seem to be.

42
00:02:41.430 --> 00:02:43.668
this is kind of paradoxical
since everyone's always trying

43
00:02:43.710 --> 00:02:45.918
to blame this on psychopathology.

44
00:02:45.960 --> 00:02:49.278
they seem to be unusually mentally sound.

45
00:02:49.320 --> 00:02:50.658
In other words. they seem to pick people

46
00:02:50.700 --> 00:02:55.700
who are particularly
strong. stable. open-minded.

47
00:02:56.280 --> 00:02:59.868
My name's Terry. I'm an experiencer.

48
00:02:59.910 --> 00:03:04.128
My name is Travis Walton
and I'm an experiencer.

49
00:03:04.170 --> 00:03:05.598
I prefer experiencer.

50
00:03:05.640 --> 00:03:07.818
I've never liked the word
abductee. I don't know why.

51
00:03:07.860 --> 00:03:09.048
it kind of creeps me out.

52
00:03:09.090 --> 00:03:13.668
Contactee sounds a
little 50-ish. 1950s weirdo.

53
00:03:13.710 --> 00:03:15.288
I had experiences.

54
00:03:15.330 --> 00:03:17.893
My name is Debbie and I'm an experiencer.

55
00:03:23.430 --> 00:03:26.058
How I got into this work

56
00:03:26.100 --> 00:03:30.948
is something that's a little
difficult for me to explain.

57
00:03:30.990 --> 00:03:34.173
It was not anything that I had planned.

58
00:03:35.250 --> 00:03:38.148
I was interested in
hypnosis and hypnotherapy

59
00:03:38.190 --> 00:03:40.248
by what I had read.

60
00:03:40.290 --> 00:03:44.388
but my heart was really in
working with cancer patients.

61
00:03:44.430 --> 00:03:48.408
Once I received the
couple of abduction cases.

62
00:03:48.450 --> 00:03:51.648
or possible abduction cases
in the beginning of my practice.

63
00:03:51.690 --> 00:03:54.828
I thought it would be very
interesting to work with people

64
00:03:54.870 --> 00:03:58.098
who feel that they have been contacted.

65
00:03:58.140 --> 00:04:02.358
So. this experience
often starts in childhood

66
00:04:02.400 --> 00:04:04.818
and follows the person
throughout their life.

67
00:04:04.860 --> 00:04:05.748
As an example.

68
00:04:05.790 --> 00:04:09.108
I am working on a case now

69
00:04:09.150 --> 00:04:12.738
where she told me that she and her sister.

70
00:04:12.780 --> 00:04:16.908
when they were young
children. shared the same dream.

71
00:04:16.950 --> 00:04:18.936
Well. then my red flag goes up.

72
00:04:18.978 --> 00:04:20.838
You know. people don't
share the same dream.

73
00:04:20.880 --> 00:04:22.743
Something may have happened.

74
00:04:29.160 --> 00:04:30.768
My name is Skyler Collins.

75
00:04:30.810 --> 00:04:32.628
I am a professional hairdresser

76
00:04:32.670 --> 00:04:35.748
and I've been doing
hair for going on 10 years.

77
00:04:35.790 --> 00:04:37.533
as well as a musician.

78
00:04:39.270 --> 00:04:41.808
I'd say that the beginning
of all of this kind of happened

79
00:04:41.850 --> 00:04:43.068
for me when I was a child.

80
00:04:43.110 --> 00:04:45.558
My sister and I are a
year and nine days apart.

81
00:04:45.600 --> 00:04:48.768
so growing up everyone
always thought we were twins.

82
00:04:48.810 --> 00:04:50.508
You know. we have a lot
of features that look similar.

83
00:04:50.550 --> 00:04:53.178
but definitely two separate personalities.

84
00:04:53.220 --> 00:04:56.028
One day we both woke up and told each other

85
00:04:56.070 --> 00:04:58.248
that we both had this similar dream.

86
00:04:58.290 --> 00:05:00.138
I think I was either six or seven.

87
00:05:00.180 --> 00:05:01.818
so she was either seven or eight.

88
00:05:01.860 --> 00:05:05.898
and this first dream we
had was like this mansion

89
00:05:05.940 --> 00:05:07.068
that we were trapped in.

90
00:05:07.110 --> 00:05:08.298
And we both confirmed

91
00:05:08.340 --> 00:05:10.548
that it was the same
setup in this living room.

92
00:05:10.590 --> 00:05:12.108
The people that were in
the dream were the same.

93
00:05:12.150 --> 00:05:12.941
Almost a year later.

94
00:05:12.983 --> 00:05:14.688
it was in the same situation again

95
00:05:14.730 --> 00:05:16.698
where we both woke up and
told each other this dream.

96
00:05:16.740 --> 00:05:17.928
This dream was a little bit different

97
00:05:17.970 --> 00:05:19.488
where we were at a family party

98
00:05:19.530 --> 00:05:22.668
and eventually all the kids
in the dream got. you know.

99
00:05:22.710 --> 00:05:25.263
absorbed into this. like. floating tornado.

100
00:05:26.640 --> 00:05:30.588
Everything went black and
then we were thrown back down.

101
00:05:30.630 --> 00:05:31.518
I just thought it was a dream.

102
00:05:31.560 --> 00:05:32.628
didn't really think anything of it.

103
00:05:32.670 --> 00:05:34.938
but apparently it's not common

104
00:05:34.980 --> 00:05:37.518
to have identical dreams with siblings.

105
00:05:37.560 --> 00:05:39.678
So. we always kind of just thought it was

106
00:05:39.720 --> 00:05:40.908
some sort of alien abduction.

107
00:05:40.950 --> 00:05:44.148
because being literally sucked
out. you know. into the sky.

108
00:05:44.190 --> 00:05:47.058
So. one of the opportunities
that was given to us

109
00:05:47.100 --> 00:05:48.828
was to go through dream regression

110
00:05:48.870 --> 00:05:50.418
and go through hypnotherapy.

111
00:05:50.460 --> 00:05:54.138
It'd be a great opportunity
to see what my options are.

112
00:05:54.180 --> 00:05:56.508
what my chances are of
figuring out if this was real or not.

113
00:05:56.550 --> 00:05:57.918
And then I can. you know.

114
00:05:57.960 --> 00:06:00.228
decide based on if it works or not.

115
00:06:00.270 --> 00:06:01.820
how to interpret what we learn.

116
00:06:17.322 --> 00:06:18.113
Hi. Sky.

117
00:06:18.155 --> 00:06:19.038
I don't think that
anything will really come

118
00:06:19.080 --> 00:06:22.158
of this hypnotherapy
'cause I'm kind of stubborn.

119
00:06:22.200 --> 00:06:25.218
I'm someone who I've never
been able to get into yoga

120
00:06:25.260 --> 00:06:26.688
because I can't let my brain go.

121
00:06:26.730 --> 00:06:28.878
I'm a very consciously moving person.

122
00:06:28.920 --> 00:06:31.668
so it's hard for me to shut
off everything around me.

123
00:06:31.710 --> 00:06:33.708
I'm gonna go through the process

124
00:06:33.750 --> 00:06:36.738
of what we're gonna do
today. take some notes.

125
00:06:36.780 --> 00:06:38.688
I'm not gonna control your mind.

126
00:06:38.730 --> 00:06:39.704
Okay.

127
00:06:39.746 --> 00:06:41.328
You're not gonna be unconscious.

128
00:06:41.370 --> 00:06:43.968
A lot of people go. "God. I
don't think I'm in hypnosis."

129
00:06:44.010 --> 00:06:47.238
"I can just get up and walk
outta here." and you can.

130
00:06:47.280 --> 00:06:49.608
but you're giving me permission

131
00:06:49.650 --> 00:06:52.370
to allow me to be your facilitator. okay?

132
00:06:52.412 --> 00:06:54.138
Okay. great. - So. just keep that in mind

133
00:06:54.180 --> 00:06:55.665
that you know...

134
00:06:58.530 --> 00:07:00.048
I think this
is a great opportunity

135
00:07:00.090 --> 00:07:01.308
to see if this was real or not

136
00:07:01.350 --> 00:07:02.748
and then I can. you know.

137
00:07:02.790 --> 00:07:05.058
decide based on if it works or not.

138
00:07:05.100 --> 00:07:06.650
how to interpret what we learn.

139
00:07:25.558 --> 00:07:30.558
You will not
be anxious or distressed.

140
00:07:31.460 --> 00:07:33.470
but you will remember everything

141
00:07:33.512 --> 00:07:36.179
and you will tell me everything.

142
00:07:38.700 --> 00:07:40.578
As the niece of Betty and Barney Hill.

143
00:07:40.620 --> 00:07:44.118
I've had a long-term interest in contact

144
00:07:44.160 --> 00:07:47.868
and attempting to discover the answers

145
00:07:47.910 --> 00:07:50.013
that I've looked for for many years.

146
00:07:53.310 --> 00:07:58.310
My aunt Betty Hill was a very
curious. very strong person.

147
00:07:58.980 --> 00:08:01.308
There was very little
that she was afraid of.

148
00:08:01.350 --> 00:08:04.068
She married a Black man in 1960.

149
00:08:04.110 --> 00:08:07.398
She was a social worker in
the state of New Hampshire

150
00:08:07.440 --> 00:08:11.523
and very active in the Civil
Rights Movement as well.

151
00:08:13.110 --> 00:08:16.788
Barney had been a very jovial person.

152
00:08:16.830 --> 00:08:19.038
He had a lot of charisma.

153
00:08:19.080 --> 00:08:23.478
and I think that this is why
in 1965 he was appointed

154
00:08:23.520 --> 00:08:26.988
to the US Civil Rights
State Advisory Commission.

155
00:08:27.030 --> 00:08:29.688
He was active in the NAACP.

156
00:08:29.730 --> 00:08:33.558
He spoke to the public
promoting civil rights.

157
00:08:33.600 --> 00:08:38.313
He'd also went on Martin Luther
King's March on Washington.

158
00:08:41.430 --> 00:08:44.358
Barney had decided to surprise Betty

159
00:08:44.400 --> 00:08:46.428
with a short vacation trip.

160
00:08:46.470 --> 00:08:50.148
So. they went to Niagara
Falls. drove up to Montreal.

161
00:08:50.190 --> 00:08:52.548
They had intended to spend the night there.

162
00:08:52.590 --> 00:08:55.518
but there was a hurricane
coming up the coast.

163
00:08:55.560 --> 00:08:59.283
so they wanted to
return home before it hit.

164
00:09:00.720 --> 00:09:04.548
As they were driving through
Northern New Hampshire.

165
00:09:04.590 --> 00:09:07.248
Betty saw a new light in the sky.

166
00:09:07.290 --> 00:09:10.128
She wondered if it might be a satellite.

167
00:09:10.170 --> 00:09:12.468
And so. she started to watch it

168
00:09:12.510 --> 00:09:16.038
as it grew larger and larger in the sky.

169
00:09:16.080 --> 00:09:18.468
She wanted Barney to stop the car

170
00:09:18.510 --> 00:09:21.468
so that she could get a
better look at this thing

171
00:09:21.510 --> 00:09:23.373
to try to identify it.

172
00:09:27.630 --> 00:09:30.018
When they finally arrived home.

173
00:09:30.060 --> 00:09:32.658
they were at least two hours later

174
00:09:32.700 --> 00:09:34.488
than they had anticipated.

175
00:09:34.530 --> 00:09:37.458
Betty's clothes were torn.

176
00:09:37.500 --> 00:09:40.608
Barney's best dress shoes
were so deeply scraped

177
00:09:40.650 --> 00:09:42.678
that he had to buy new shoes.

178
00:09:42.720 --> 00:09:46.848
The watches they were wearing
that night never ran again.

179
00:09:46.890 --> 00:09:50.238
Betty especially wanted
to learn more and more.

180
00:09:50.280 --> 00:09:53.958
Barney unfortunately
developed what we know today

181
00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:56.328
as post-traumatic stress disorder.

182
00:09:56.370 --> 00:10:00.948
He developed a bleeding
ulcer. high blood pressure.

183
00:10:00.990 --> 00:10:03.288
and these things would not recede

184
00:10:03.330 --> 00:10:05.538
with traditional medical treatment.

185
00:10:05.580 --> 00:10:09.408
He was greatly distressed
by his conscious recall

186
00:10:09.450 --> 00:10:12.618
of feeling that he was going to be captured

187
00:10:12.660 --> 00:10:13.878
and then having evidence

188
00:10:13.920 --> 00:10:16.593
that he might have indeed been captured.

189
00:10:18.060 --> 00:10:21.528
He was referred to a renowned psychiatrist

190
00:10:21.570 --> 00:10:25.698
in Boston. Massachusetts.
Dr. Benjamin Simon.

191
00:10:25.740 --> 00:10:30.048
He worked with veterans
returning from the war

192
00:10:30.090 --> 00:10:31.638
during World War II.

193
00:10:31.680 --> 00:10:34.188
He used deep trans hypnosis

194
00:10:34.230 --> 00:10:37.698
to help his patients resolve the trauma

195
00:10:37.740 --> 00:10:39.738
that they had experienced.

196
00:10:39.780 --> 00:10:43.368
Betty and Barney. under separate hypnosis.

197
00:10:43.410 --> 00:10:45.153
relived the same events.

198
00:10:54.180 --> 00:10:57.713
We are driving along.
I don't know where we are.

199
00:11:02.818 --> 00:11:06.197
I don't even know how we got here.

200
00:11:06.239 --> 00:11:08.450
We've been driving and
I don't know how long

201
00:11:08.492 --> 00:11:09.886
and we haven't even been talking

202
00:11:09.928 --> 00:11:11.757
when I've just been feeling a feeling

203
00:11:11.799 --> 00:11:14.299
that something's gonna happen.

204
00:11:16.536 --> 00:11:19.291
You go deeper
and deeper. deeper asleep.

205
00:11:19.333 --> 00:11:21.523
You will remember everything

206
00:11:21.565 --> 00:11:25.316
and you will tell me everything.

207
00:11:25.358 --> 00:11:26.608
Yes.

208
00:11:28.213 --> 00:11:31.383
I pulled over to the side of the road.

209
00:11:33.660 --> 00:11:37.547
Betty is trying to make me
think this is a flying saucer.

210
00:11:39.270 --> 00:11:40.353
And I don't.

211
00:11:42.293 --> 00:11:45.588
I try to maintain control

212
00:11:45.630 --> 00:11:48.573
so Betty cannot tell I am scared.

213
00:11:50.520 --> 00:11:51.873
God. I'm scared.

214
00:11:54.164 --> 00:11:57.675
They won't talk to me.
- Who won't talk to you?

215
00:11:57.717 --> 00:12:00.167
The men that
are standing in the road.

216
00:12:03.445 --> 00:12:05.380
Did they have
faces like other people?

217
00:12:05.422 --> 00:12:07.586
His eyes were slanted.

218
00:12:07.628 --> 00:12:11.238
I see it so. His eyes were slanted.

219
00:12:11.280 --> 00:12:13.203
But not like a Chinese.

220
00:12:15.480 --> 00:12:16.893
I gotta get my gun.

221
00:12:20.098 --> 00:12:21.383
Really gotta get my gun. - All right.

222
00:12:23.370 --> 00:12:25.143
Calm down. Relax.

223
00:12:26.160 --> 00:12:26.993
Deeply relaxed.

224
00:12:30.030 --> 00:12:32.268
What was Betty doing all this time?

225
00:12:32.310 --> 00:12:35.072
He's trying to start
the car and it won't start.

226
00:12:35.114 --> 00:12:37.365
And the men are coming towards us.

227
00:12:37.407 --> 00:12:39.498
And I think. well...

228
00:12:39.540 --> 00:12:41.088
I can get away form this.

229
00:12:41.130 --> 00:12:42.498
If I can get the car door open.

230
00:12:42.540 --> 00:12:44.501
I can run in the woods and hide.

231
00:12:44.543 --> 00:12:48.948
And the men come up
and they open it for me.

232
00:12:48.990 --> 00:12:49.938
This creature.

233
00:12:49.980 --> 00:12:52.655
this leader is telling me something.

234
00:12:52.697 --> 00:12:54.618
He's telling you something. How?

235
00:12:54.660 --> 00:12:56.658
How's it getting it to you?

236
00:12:56.700 --> 00:12:58.698
I can see it in his face.

237
00:12:58.740 --> 00:13:01.159
Do you see his lips move? Yes.

238
00:13:01.201 --> 00:13:03.269
No. he's lips aren't moving.

239
00:13:03.311 --> 00:13:05.870
How could you be
sure he was telling you this?

240
00:13:05.912 --> 00:13:07.579
His eyes.

241
00:13:10.232 --> 00:13:11.065
His eyes.

242
00:13:13.277 --> 00:13:16.338
He says. "You don't
have any reason to be afraid.

243
00:13:16.380 --> 00:13:18.315
We're not going to harm you."

244
00:13:18.357 --> 00:13:21.218
And they're taking me up to the object.

245
00:13:21.260 --> 00:13:23.835
I don't wanna go on it.

246
00:13:23.877 --> 00:13:26.958
I don't know what's
gonna happen if I go on it.

247
00:13:27.000 --> 00:13:28.848
Did you feel you
were going to be attacked

248
00:13:28.890 --> 00:13:31.338
in any way? - No.

249
00:13:31.380 --> 00:13:32.680
I was laying on the table.

250
00:13:34.680 --> 00:13:38.538
The examiner unzips my dress off.

251
00:13:38.580 --> 00:13:42.667
I lie down on the table on my back

252
00:13:42.709 --> 00:13:46.626
and the examiner has a
long needle in his hand.

253
00:13:48.670 --> 00:13:52.640
It's bigger than any needle I've ever seen.

254
00:13:52.682 --> 00:13:56.471
And my fly
was open and I thought

255
00:13:56.513 --> 00:14:00.430
are they putting a cup
around my private parts?

256
00:14:01.378 --> 00:14:04.400
And he sticks a needle into my navel.

257
00:14:04.442 --> 00:14:06.881
And I'm crying and I tell him it's hurting.

258
00:14:06.923 --> 00:14:10.090
and hurting. and hurting. take it out.

259
00:14:11.250 --> 00:14:13.218
And then the leader.

260
00:14:13.260 --> 00:14:15.600
he goes over and he puts his hand.

261
00:14:16.620 --> 00:14:19.615
runs his hand in front
of my eyes and he says.

262
00:14:19.657 --> 00:14:22.257
"I'll be all right. I won't feel it."

263
00:14:25.770 --> 00:14:28.308
And all the pain goes away.

264
00:14:28.350 --> 00:14:30.710
I asked the leader. I said.

265
00:14:30.752 --> 00:14:32.670
why did he stick the needle in my navel?

266
00:14:32.712 --> 00:14:34.966
And he said. "It was a pregnancy test."

267
00:14:35.008 --> 00:14:38.744
And I said that was no pregnancy test here.

268
00:14:48.043 --> 00:14:50.348
I thought. how funny.

269
00:14:50.390 --> 00:14:54.048
if I keep real quiet and real still.

270
00:14:54.090 --> 00:14:57.183
I won't be harmed and it will be over.

271
00:14:58.605 --> 00:15:01.188
He went over and did something

272
00:15:01.230 --> 00:15:04.308
and the metal of the wall.

273
00:15:04.350 --> 00:15:09.198
there was an opening
and he pulled down a map.

274
00:15:09.240 --> 00:15:13.248
He asked me. had I ever
seen a map like this before?

275
00:15:13.290 --> 00:15:16.608
It was an oblong map.

276
00:15:16.650 --> 00:15:21.168
And he said that the heavy
lines were trade routes.

277
00:15:21.210 --> 00:15:26.210
And then the other lines. the solid lines.

278
00:15:26.280 --> 00:15:29.643
were places they went occasionally.

279
00:15:30.900 --> 00:15:34.878
The broken lines were expeditions.

280
00:15:34.920 --> 00:15:38.478
I asked him where was his home port?

281
00:15:38.520 --> 00:15:43.206
He said. "Where are you on this map?"

282
00:15:43.248 --> 00:15:47.778
I looked and I laughed
and I said. "I don't know."

283
00:15:47.820 --> 00:15:52.820
So. he said. "Well then. if
you don't know where you are.

284
00:15:53.231 --> 00:15:58.231
there wouldn't be any point
of my telling you where I am."

285
00:16:01.830 --> 00:16:05.118
Later. Marjorie Fish. a brilliant woman.

286
00:16:05.160 --> 00:16:10.008
took that star map and
did years of research

287
00:16:10.050 --> 00:16:14.823
to try to find the stars
that Betty had sketched.

288
00:16:16.920 --> 00:16:19.728
And then in 1971.

289
00:16:19.770 --> 00:16:23.343
there was a new
astronomical catalog published.

290
00:16:24.390 --> 00:16:26.958
There were now three stars on the map

291
00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:29.778
that hadn't been there before.

292
00:16:29.820 --> 00:16:32.028
She added the new stars

293
00:16:32.070 --> 00:16:36.378
and she had a match for Betty's star map.

294
00:16:36.420 --> 00:16:41.420
The two stars in the foreground
were Zeta Reticuli 1 and 2.

295
00:16:47.550 --> 00:16:48.863
Where are you now?

296
00:16:50.580 --> 00:16:55.278
I open my eyes and there is the car.

297
00:16:55.320 --> 00:16:59.493
And Delsy is in a tight
ball under the seat.

298
00:17:03.000 --> 00:17:06.528
I see Betty. she gets into the car.

299
00:17:06.570 --> 00:17:11.570
And I am grinning at her
and she is grinning back at me.

300
00:17:11.727 --> 00:17:14.898
And we both seem so elated.

301
00:17:14.940 --> 00:17:18.393
And I'm thinking it isn't too bad.

302
00:17:19.260 --> 00:17:22.788
How funny. I have no reason to fear.

303
00:17:22.830 --> 00:17:25.043
And we look and I see a
bright moon and I laugh and say.

304
00:17:31.432 --> 00:17:33.265
"Well. there it goes."

305
00:17:34.552 --> 00:17:35.803
And I'm happy.

306
00:17:50.220 --> 00:17:51.468
I'm Dr. Michael Masters.

307
00:17:51.510 --> 00:17:55.428
I'm a professor of biological
anthropology at Montana Tech.

308
00:17:55.470 --> 00:17:57.468
As a paleoanthropologist.

309
00:17:57.510 --> 00:18:01.008
I would be doing things almost
identical to what's described

310
00:18:01.050 --> 00:18:02.600
in reports of close encounters.

311
00:18:06.270 --> 00:18:09.978
I'd be taking skin samples.
hair samples. fecal samples.

312
00:18:10.020 --> 00:18:13.188
which could be what gives
rise to the anal probing aspect

313
00:18:13.230 --> 00:18:14.448
of this phenomenon.

314
00:18:14.490 --> 00:18:16.218
I would be studying culture.

315
00:18:16.260 --> 00:18:17.748
I would be studying the things

316
00:18:17.790 --> 00:18:19.578
that don't preserve in the fossil record.

317
00:18:19.620 --> 00:18:23.148
things that we could only
know by being a part of that past

318
00:18:23.190 --> 00:18:26.118
and observing those individuals

319
00:18:26.160 --> 00:18:29.463
and those cultures as
living. breathing things.

320
00:18:32.730 --> 00:18:35.868
I interpret their behaviors
in the context of this lens

321
00:18:35.910 --> 00:18:39.888
that I see through. but
what they do. how they do it.

322
00:18:39.930 --> 00:18:41.208
when they do it.

323
00:18:41.250 --> 00:18:42.888
all of these things seem to indicate

324
00:18:42.930 --> 00:18:44.680
that there's some research mission.

325
00:18:46.830 --> 00:18:50.838
that there's some attempt at
discovering their own history

326
00:18:50.880 --> 00:18:53.943
and where they came
from in the deep future.

327
00:18:57.030 --> 00:19:00.318
Perhaps it stems from my
own bias as an anthropologist.

328
00:19:00.360 --> 00:19:02.898
as a biological anthropologist.

329
00:19:02.940 --> 00:19:04.590
That's what I would do with this.

330
00:19:07.860 --> 00:19:09.198
What has happened to these people

331
00:19:09.240 --> 00:19:11.178
is what they say has happened to them.

332
00:19:11.220 --> 00:19:15.078
even though I fully recognize
that that's not possible

333
00:19:15.120 --> 00:19:18.333
in the worldview in which
they and I were raised.

334
00:19:19.440 --> 00:19:21.173
Well.
then. how is it possible?

335
00:19:22.050 --> 00:19:23.808
Well. that's the question. isn't it?

336
00:19:23.850 --> 00:19:26.028
Either we try to shrink the phenomenon

337
00:19:26.070 --> 00:19:29.808
into something where it.
as far as I can tell. won't fit.

338
00:19:29.850 --> 00:19:32.800
or we're gonna have to stretch
our notions of the possible.

339
00:19:46.170 --> 00:19:49.338
I passed five different
lie detector tests

340
00:19:49.380 --> 00:19:51.468
from three different examiners.

341
00:19:51.510 --> 00:19:53.538
all with years

342
00:19:53.580 --> 00:19:57.693
of law enforcement
experience as interrogators.

343
00:19:59.520 --> 00:20:01.458
We had been working some long. hard days.

344
00:20:01.500 --> 00:20:05.868
and just as usual at that time period.

345
00:20:05.910 --> 00:20:09.048
we worked up until dark.
packed up our equipment.

346
00:20:09.090 --> 00:20:10.488
We were headed home

347
00:20:10.530 --> 00:20:14.583
and we saw this glow
through the trees up ahead.

348
00:20:16.230 --> 00:20:19.938
The strangeness of the
glow kind of made me think

349
00:20:19.980 --> 00:20:23.658
that perhaps deer hunters were
camped up there on the ridge.

350
00:20:23.700 --> 00:20:26.475
You know how you can
have a lantern inside of a tent

351
00:20:26.517 --> 00:20:28.728
and it puts off a glow?

352
00:20:28.770 --> 00:20:31.248
But there was just something odd about it.

353
00:20:31.290 --> 00:20:33.588
You know. the idea that skeptics put forth

354
00:20:33.630 --> 00:20:36.288
that what we really saw
was the planet Jupiter

355
00:20:36.330 --> 00:20:38.688
in the distance. and that's absurd.

356
00:20:38.730 --> 00:20:43.308
This was a clearly defined
metallic object hovering there

357
00:20:43.350 --> 00:20:45.828
in the clearing less
than a hundred feet away.

358
00:20:45.870 --> 00:20:46.968
Everybody knew what it was.

359
00:20:47.010 --> 00:20:51.175
Immediately. one of the
men. Alan Dallas. yelled out.

360
00:20:51.217 --> 00:20:52.518
"It's a flying saucer!"

361
00:20:52.560 --> 00:20:56.283
I mean. there was no doubt
of what we were looking at.

362
00:20:58.140 --> 00:21:00.370
I threw open the door and headed towards it

363
00:21:01.330 --> 00:21:04.758
and there was a little bit of bravado.

364
00:21:04.800 --> 00:21:06.708
maybe a little show off going on there.

365
00:21:06.750 --> 00:21:09.468
but I thought this thing would take off

366
00:21:09.510 --> 00:21:11.193
before I got that close.

367
00:21:12.270 --> 00:21:14.028
Looking up at it.

368
00:21:14.070 --> 00:21:17.028
it was extremely shiny

369
00:21:17.070 --> 00:21:20.358
and giving off light at the same time.

370
00:21:20.400 --> 00:21:23.328
The noise it was making was pretty scary.

371
00:21:23.370 --> 00:21:25.608
Basically. off the range of human hearing

372
00:21:25.650 --> 00:21:29.688
on the high and the low
end.

373
00:21:29.730 --> 00:21:32.208
I decided to run back to the truck.

374
00:21:32.250 --> 00:21:34.698
And when I stood up to run back.

375
00:21:34.740 --> 00:21:39.738
I closed the distance between
my upper body and the craft.

376
00:21:39.780 --> 00:21:41.860
And that's when this blast hit me.

377
00:21:44.490 --> 00:21:46.578
It threw me 15 or 20 feet.

378
00:21:46.620 --> 00:21:50.373
John said my body fell in
a clump like a sack of meat.

379
00:21:52.170 --> 00:21:55.698
They said they panicked and took off.

380
00:21:55.740 --> 00:21:57.798
And when they expressed the idea

381
00:21:57.840 --> 00:22:02.568
that one of our men is
lost. you know. maybe killed.

382
00:22:02.610 --> 00:22:05.058
you know. the sheriff and his men.

383
00:22:05.100 --> 00:22:06.750
their attention really perked up.

384
00:22:07.740 --> 00:22:10.218
What do you mean maybe killed?

385
00:22:10.260 --> 00:22:12.828
The suspicion that this was
some kind of a cover story

386
00:22:12.870 --> 00:22:15.198
for murder began almost immediately.

387
00:22:15.240 --> 00:22:17.695
So. the men just protested. saying.

388
00:22:17.737 --> 00:22:19.488
"We're telling the truth.

389
00:22:19.530 --> 00:22:21.708
We'll take any kind of test you want."

390
00:22:21.750 --> 00:22:23.958
The sheriff took 'em up on it.

391
00:22:24.000 --> 00:22:26.898
So all the men passed
their lie detector tests

392
00:22:26.940 --> 00:22:30.903
and the sheriff organized a search.

393
00:22:33.810 --> 00:22:36.708
Eventually. they increased
the number of searchers

394
00:22:36.750 --> 00:22:38.268
and there were men on horseback.

395
00:22:38.310 --> 00:22:40.728
aircraft. helicopters. airplanes.

396
00:22:40.770 --> 00:22:42.888
They even brought in the tracking dogs

397
00:22:42.930 --> 00:22:44.478
from the local prison.

398
00:22:44.520 --> 00:22:47.238
Those dogs were unable to find a trail

399
00:22:47.280 --> 00:22:50.028
beyond the edge of the road

400
00:22:50.070 --> 00:22:54.018
where I'd gotten out of the
truck up to where my body fell.

401
00:22:54.060 --> 00:22:55.878
And that was the end of the trail.

402
00:22:55.920 --> 00:22:58.963
So. that was pretty significant.

403
00:23:06.540 --> 00:23:09.183
After losing consciousness.

404
00:23:10.020 --> 00:23:12.558
the very next memory that I had

405
00:23:12.600 --> 00:23:17.148
was a foggy sort of
perception of where I was.

406
00:23:17.190 --> 00:23:19.428
The pain I was feeling led me to believe

407
00:23:19.470 --> 00:23:22.180
that I somehow got hurt in fleeing

408
00:23:23.130 --> 00:23:25.758
and that they had taken me to the hospital.

409
00:23:25.800 --> 00:23:27.138
And so. when my vision cleared

410
00:23:27.180 --> 00:23:28.638
and I was finally able to focus.

411
00:23:28.680 --> 00:23:32.118
I could see that these
definitely were not doctors.

412
00:23:32.160 --> 00:23:35.478
That this were these strange
creatures looking at me

413
00:23:35.520 --> 00:23:38.694
and I instantly became hysterical.

414
00:23:43.950 --> 00:23:45.513
It's not easy to talk about.

415
00:23:50.100 --> 00:23:51.738
It was very claustrophobic.

416
00:23:51.780 --> 00:23:54.558
I was having a lot of difficulty breathing

417
00:23:54.600 --> 00:23:58.548
and I associated this
feeling of suffocation

418
00:23:58.590 --> 00:24:03.590
with the faces of these beings.

419
00:24:03.750 --> 00:24:07.218
To this day. you know. in my entire life.

420
00:24:07.260 --> 00:24:10.233
that was the greatest
fear I've ever experienced.

421
00:24:12.570 --> 00:24:16.428
These small beings. and
they were all the same size.

422
00:24:16.470 --> 00:24:19.788
cooperating and moving sort of in unison.

423
00:24:19.830 --> 00:24:23.358
led me to think that they
were probably telepathic

424
00:24:23.400 --> 00:24:27.738
to each other and
attempting to be so with me.

425
00:24:27.780 --> 00:24:32.780
but it was my neurological
injury of being hit by this beam

426
00:24:33.120 --> 00:24:37.188
on this craft that made it
to where they couldn't affect

427
00:24:37.230 --> 00:24:40.098
some mind control sort of a thing.

428
00:24:40.140 --> 00:24:45.140
And something that adds to
that was the brainwave scan

429
00:24:45.390 --> 00:24:47.568
that I had when I was returned.

430
00:24:47.610 --> 00:24:51.018
It showed evidence of
some anomalous patterns

431
00:24:51.060 --> 00:24:52.593
that later disappeared.

432
00:24:55.530 --> 00:24:59.718
My anxiety about subsequent
bad health effects. you know.

433
00:24:59.760 --> 00:25:04.398
that there would be some sort
of premature aging or cancer.

434
00:25:04.440 --> 00:25:08.028
radiation. sickness. some
sort of bizarre infection.

435
00:25:08.070 --> 00:25:09.948
None of that materialized.

436
00:25:09.990 --> 00:25:13.758
On the contrary. I didn't get sick at all.

437
00:25:13.800 --> 00:25:16.728
I never called in sick
one time in 40 years.

438
00:25:16.770 --> 00:25:21.348
Is that proof that they
did some kind of repairs

439
00:25:21.390 --> 00:25:23.478
that might have resulted
in a little bit of a tuneup

440
00:25:23.520 --> 00:25:25.068
or a health benefit?

441
00:25:25.110 --> 00:25:26.058
Possible.

442
00:25:26.100 --> 00:25:27.978
Is it proof? No.

443
00:25:28.020 --> 00:25:29.718
You know. I try to live a healthy life.

444
00:25:29.760 --> 00:25:30.888
It could have been due to that.

445
00:25:30.930 --> 00:25:35.328
but it was certainly the
opposite of coming down

446
00:25:35.370 --> 00:25:36.933
with bad effects.

447
00:25:41.520 --> 00:25:43.308
I'm constantly confronted by people

448
00:25:43.350 --> 00:25:44.628
who have all the answers

449
00:25:44.670 --> 00:25:48.288
and they wanna tell me who these beings are

450
00:25:48.330 --> 00:25:51.168
and what they represent.

451
00:25:51.210 --> 00:25:53.238
I don't think anybody really knows that.

452
00:25:53.280 --> 00:25:55.908
and intentionally so.

453
00:25:55.950 --> 00:25:58.068
I think these beings are holding back

454
00:25:58.110 --> 00:25:59.628
on that kind of information.

455
00:25:59.670 --> 00:26:03.498
I don't believe in the
idea that these beings

456
00:26:03.540 --> 00:26:07.248
have been for several
hundred years creeping around.

457
00:26:07.290 --> 00:26:10.008
trying to come up with a way to take over.

458
00:26:10.050 --> 00:26:11.418
That just doesn't make sense.

459
00:26:11.460 --> 00:26:13.368
If they felt nothing for us.

460
00:26:13.410 --> 00:26:16.068
it would be very simple to eliminate us.

461
00:26:16.110 --> 00:26:19.338
There wouldn't be dog
fights with our fighter jets

462
00:26:19.380 --> 00:26:21.918
and their craft in the sky.

463
00:26:21.960 --> 00:26:26.960
They're way superior to that
level of combat or hostility.

464
00:26:27.990 --> 00:26:31.435
I just don't think it's the way it is.

465
00:26:40.286 --> 00:26:45.286
10. nine. eight. seven. six.

466
00:26:45.870 --> 00:26:49.038
You're almost there.

467
00:26:49.080 --> 00:26:54.080
And five. four. three. two. one. and zero.

468
00:26:59.400 --> 00:27:04.400
Allow yourself now to
gently drift back in time

469
00:27:05.980 --> 00:27:08.410
to the time when you were a little girl

470
00:27:09.690 --> 00:27:12.228
of about seven years old.

471
00:27:12.270 --> 00:27:15.378
And as you come closer to the house.

472
00:27:15.420 --> 00:27:20.420
describe where you are in
that house and how everybody

473
00:27:20.700 --> 00:27:22.533
and everything looks around you.

474
00:27:30.129 --> 00:27:32.629
I'm by my bunk bed. - Mm-hmm.

475
00:27:34.170 --> 00:27:36.153
The door's cracked open.

476
00:27:38.790 --> 00:27:40.938
Not really like standing on the floor.

477
00:27:40.980 --> 00:27:43.398
I'm kind of like looking at it

478
00:27:43.440 --> 00:27:45.618
from the corner of the room up top.

479
00:27:45.660 --> 00:27:47.478
It's very quiet.

480
00:27:47.520 --> 00:27:49.668
I don't think anyone's home.

481
00:27:49.710 --> 00:27:54.710
Trying to like be asleep.
but like super restless.

482
00:27:57.540 --> 00:28:01.083
It doesn't feel calm
anymore. it feels really.

483
00:28:02.698 --> 00:28:05.088
I just feel like really uneasy.

484
00:28:05.130 --> 00:28:06.258
I just feel like scared.

485
00:28:06.300 --> 00:28:08.868
I keep like glancing
over at my closet I had

486
00:28:08.910 --> 00:28:09.701
when I was a kid.

487
00:28:09.743 --> 00:28:10.923
It was always scary to me.

488
00:28:12.030 --> 00:28:14.868
Just like keep seeing it over to the side.

489
00:28:14.910 --> 00:28:16.728
My closet's just really weird.

490
00:28:16.770 --> 00:28:19.028
My eyes just can't relax right now.

491
00:28:19.070 --> 00:28:20.388
It just feels like lightning.

492
00:28:20.430 --> 00:28:22.159
It just feels bright like lightning.

493
00:28:27.674 --> 00:28:28.465
I don't know why.

494
00:28:28.507 --> 00:28:30.228
I just really just can't
stop looking at my closet

495
00:28:30.270 --> 00:28:31.443
in my eyes right now.

496
00:28:34.320 --> 00:28:38.913
Just try to describe what
is there. what you're sensing.

497
00:28:40.916 --> 00:28:43.668
I just feel super scared.

498
00:28:43.710 --> 00:28:45.048
but it's like I don't wanna go over there.

499
00:28:45.090 --> 00:28:47.478
but there's just like this light.

500
00:28:47.520 --> 00:28:51.558
it's like a bluish-white light.

501
00:28:51.600 --> 00:28:55.008
I get this blue-white
description all the time.

502
00:28:55.050 --> 00:28:58.098
Usually when people
describe a light shining down.

503
00:28:58.140 --> 00:28:59.688
it's coming from a craft.

504
00:28:59.730 --> 00:29:01.758
but I don't suggest that to her.

505
00:29:01.800 --> 00:29:05.088
She didn't say it. she didn't say a craft.

506
00:29:05.130 --> 00:29:06.858
but she just saw the blue-white light.

507
00:29:06.900 --> 00:29:11.900
The closet's black. but I
can see this like gray light.

508
00:29:15.120 --> 00:29:16.128
It's not even like a light.

509
00:29:16.170 --> 00:29:18.408
but it's like nothing's
reflecting on it but it's there

510
00:29:18.450 --> 00:29:22.968
and I can see just like
this gray around the black.

511
00:29:23.010 --> 00:29:27.163
Now get a sense of that gray.

512
00:29:30.090 --> 00:29:33.048
It feels just like staring.

513
00:29:33.090 --> 00:29:36.963
but it's not like a scary feeling of that.

