769
00:41:19.140 --> 00:41:21.495
and I could see there
were these flashes of lights

770
00:41:21.537 --> 00:41:25.128
and I could see tracks
of tears down his face.

771
00:41:25.170 --> 00:41:26.628
and all that feeling of calm

772
00:41:26.670 --> 00:41:29.028
and apathy that I felt earlier was gone

773
00:41:29.070 --> 00:41:31.098
and there was nothing
now but abject terror.

774
00:41:31.140 --> 00:41:34.938
I got to my knees and I
pulled back my flap of the tent

775
00:41:34.980 --> 00:41:37.383
and I look out and I noticed two things.

776
00:41:38.790 --> 00:41:42.228
The craft that had been 3.000 feet above us

777
00:41:42.270 --> 00:41:45.678
had now descended and is
just 30 feet over the metal.

778
00:41:45.720 --> 00:41:49.458
And I noticed what I thought first

779
00:41:49.500 --> 00:41:51.663
to be children walking around the metal.

780
00:41:52.710 --> 00:41:53.665
And I asked Toby. I said.

781
00:41:53.707 --> 00:41:55.488
"Toby. man. what are
these kids doing out here

782
00:41:55.530 --> 00:41:58.728
in the middle of this metal
in the middle of the night?"

783
00:41:58.770 --> 00:42:01.878
And he said. "Man. those
ain't no little kids. Terry.

784
00:42:01.920 --> 00:42:04.038
They're not human beings.

785
00:42:04.080 --> 00:42:07.227
They took us and they hurt
us. don't you remember?"

786
00:42:09.750 --> 00:42:13.023
I became aware that I was in
some type of operating room.

787
00:42:14.550 --> 00:42:19.008
There was a white-domed
ceiling and a white pedestal table.

788
00:42:19.050 --> 00:42:20.028
And I recall thinking

789
00:42:20.070 --> 00:42:22.668
that the table should
have been cold to the touch.

790
00:42:22.710 --> 00:42:24.378
but it wasn't. it was warm.

791
00:42:24.420 --> 00:42:25.848
and it was probably warm

792
00:42:25.890 --> 00:42:29.388
from the bodies that
had been on prior to me.

793
00:42:29.430 --> 00:42:32.538
I'm darting my eyes around
because it's all I can move

794
00:42:32.580 --> 00:42:35.118
and trying to take in as much as possible.

795
00:42:35.160 --> 00:42:37.908
I saw not only that there
were the little grays around.

796
00:42:37.950 --> 00:42:39.198
six foot tall.

797
00:42:39.240 --> 00:42:41.718
pinkish-colored guy that
seemed to be in charge.

798
00:42:41.760 --> 00:42:44.553
but there was human
beings aboard this craft.

799
00:42:45.600 --> 00:42:49.818
five. what appeared to be military.

800
00:42:49.860 --> 00:42:53.838
guys 18 to early 20s.
military style haircuts.

801
00:42:53.880 --> 00:42:57.528
tan flight suits. orange insignias.

802
00:42:57.570 --> 00:42:59.898
And I was trying to make
eye contact with them

803
00:42:59.940 --> 00:43:01.128
and they would not look at us.

804
00:43:01.170 --> 00:43:03.153
they would not look in our direction.

805
00:43:04.530 --> 00:43:06.258
When they took me into the room

806
00:43:06.300 --> 00:43:08.553
and did the medical experimentation on me.

807
00:43:09.450 --> 00:43:12.333
there was an insectoid-like creature.

808
00:43:13.560 --> 00:43:15.123
maybe seven feet tall.

809
00:43:16.770 --> 00:43:20.388
So. there were a couple
of different types of entities

810
00:43:20.430 --> 00:43:22.818
and I think that they
were all working in concert.

811
00:43:22.860 --> 00:43:26.118
I have an opinion about the
grays that I should add here.

812
00:43:26.160 --> 00:43:28.398
or at least the ones that
I came in contact with.

813
00:43:28.440 --> 00:43:30.738
I don't believe that
they are sentient beings

814
00:43:30.780 --> 00:43:32.418
like you and I are.

815
00:43:32.460 --> 00:43:34.818
I think they're maybe a combination of AI.

816
00:43:34.860 --> 00:43:38.688
nanotechnology. maybe quantum computing.

817
00:43:38.730 --> 00:43:41.793
but I don't think that
they're living sentient beings.

818
00:43:47.280 --> 00:43:50.058
In terms of trying to
explain actual phenomenon

819
00:43:50.100 --> 00:43:51.798
that's been recorded.

820
00:43:51.840 --> 00:43:54.198
I feel like a technological answer

821
00:43:54.240 --> 00:43:57.183
is probably the easiest answer.

822
00:43:58.350 --> 00:44:01.458
There is a reason that NASA sends robots

823
00:44:01.500 --> 00:44:02.988
to explore outer space.

824
00:44:03.030 --> 00:44:06.348
I mean. it's really handy to
be able to build a technology

825
00:44:06.390 --> 00:44:08.388
that's perfectly suited for the environment

826
00:44:08.430 --> 00:44:09.798
that you're gonna be exploring.

827
00:44:09.840 --> 00:44:13.008
And so. if I were going
to explore an alien world.

828
00:44:13.050 --> 00:44:15.108
I would definitely send a robotic probe

829
00:44:15.150 --> 00:44:17.328
because as a biological creature.

830
00:44:17.370 --> 00:44:20.328
it's much harder for
me to change my biology

831
00:44:20.370 --> 00:44:23.358
than it is for me to build a technology

832
00:44:23.400 --> 00:44:24.798
that's gonna be perfectly suited

833
00:44:24.840 --> 00:44:26.808
for whatever environment I'm headed to.

834
00:44:26.850 --> 00:44:29.238
whether it's the hot depths of Venus

835
00:44:29.280 --> 00:44:31.728
or whether I'm on a freezing cold Mars.

836
00:44:31.770 --> 00:44:33.978
you can build the robots
to suit the environment

837
00:44:34.020 --> 00:44:35.508
that you're headed for.

838
00:44:35.550 --> 00:44:37.908
This technology is so smart

839
00:44:37.950 --> 00:44:40.668
that it doesn't even
necessarily care about us.

840
00:44:40.710 --> 00:44:42.588
And so. it makes decisions

841
00:44:42.630 --> 00:44:44.598
without really considering people.

842
00:44:44.640 --> 00:44:47.103
And sometimes that's
pretty catastrophic for us.

843
00:44:48.780 --> 00:44:50.928
In "Robopocalypse." the reason we survive

844
00:44:50.970 --> 00:44:53.358
is because of our human adaptability

845
00:44:53.400 --> 00:44:57.498
and our basic low-level
devious intelligence

846
00:44:57.540 --> 00:44:59.178
and will to survive.

847
00:44:59.220 --> 00:45:00.528
And that's kept us going

848
00:45:00.570 --> 00:45:02.208
for a couple hundred thousand years.

849
00:45:02.250 --> 00:45:04.188
and hopefully it'll keep us going

850
00:45:04.230 --> 00:45:06.138
through any alien robot uprisings

851
00:45:06.180 --> 00:45:07.830
that we might face in the future.

852
00:45:11.820 --> 00:45:14.538
It's possible that they
would have a technology

853
00:45:14.580 --> 00:45:17.928
where they could come
up with a synthetic robot

854
00:45:17.970 --> 00:45:18.978
of some sort.

855
00:45:19.020 --> 00:45:22.698
I really think that if the
intention was to stand in place

856
00:45:22.740 --> 00:45:23.958
of a living being.

857
00:45:24.000 --> 00:45:26.688
it would be something that
resemble humans the most

858
00:45:26.730 --> 00:45:29.493
that I would be less combative with.

859
00:45:31.710 --> 00:45:36.710
The idea that these beings
somehow evolved away from emotion

860
00:45:38.430 --> 00:45:40.188
and no longer feel it and you know.

861
00:45:40.230 --> 00:45:43.068
some people even claim
that they are curious about us

862
00:45:43.110 --> 00:45:45.648
because we feel emotion and
they don't feel that anymore.

863
00:45:45.690 --> 00:45:47.478
But here's the deal.

864
00:45:47.520 --> 00:45:52.520
once an intelligent sentient
being is capable of telepathy.

865
00:45:53.940 --> 00:45:56.448
facial expressions becomes superfluous.

866
00:45:56.490 --> 00:45:59.088
On the contrary. rather than
no longer feeling emotion.

867
00:45:59.130 --> 00:46:03.468
it might be that they
feel it in a much higher.

868
00:46:03.510 --> 00:46:05.373
more intense level than we do.

869
00:46:06.930 --> 00:46:08.958
When this thing looked at me.

870
00:46:09.000 --> 00:46:13.608
he seemed surprised that I was so upset.

871
00:46:13.650 --> 00:46:15.858
He kind of cocked his
head at me a little bit

872
00:46:15.900 --> 00:46:19.728
and then all of a sudden I
got hit with this emotion bomb

873
00:46:19.770 --> 00:46:24.708
and it was as if every emotion
that a human could feel.

874
00:46:24.750 --> 00:46:29.658
he was blasting at me in some lame attempt

875
00:46:29.700 --> 00:46:33.363
to feel something like for me.

876
00:46:35.310 --> 00:46:38.763
My experience happened in June of 1977.

877
00:46:39.900 --> 00:46:43.068
Steven Spielberg's movie
"Close Encounters" came out

878
00:46:43.110 --> 00:46:45.108
in November that same year.

879
00:46:45.150 --> 00:46:49.488
It was 30 years before I
felt comfortable enough

880
00:46:49.530 --> 00:46:51.798
to watch the movie. but when I did.

881
00:46:51.840 --> 00:46:54.378
I was struck by a number of parallels.

882
00:46:54.420 --> 00:46:57.078
I was absolutely blown away by the fact

883
00:46:57.120 --> 00:47:01.758
that he portrayed
these men in flight suits.

884
00:47:01.800 --> 00:47:02.988
They weren't tanned.

885
00:47:03.030 --> 00:47:07.398
but there was obviously an
exchange of men and women

886
00:47:07.440 --> 00:47:12.408
and aliens working in
concert toward a common goal.

887
00:47:12.450 --> 00:47:16.068
And that's kind of the
takeaway from Spielberg's movie.

888
00:47:16.110 --> 00:47:21.048
is all of these entities working in concert

889
00:47:21.090 --> 00:47:23.013
towards some common agenda.

890
00:47:24.030 --> 00:47:26.330
And God. I'd love to
know what that agenda is.

891
00:47:28.920 --> 00:47:31.788
Documentary.
that's a pilot half hour thing.

892
00:47:31.830 --> 00:47:32.928
I should do it real quick.

893
00:47:32.970 --> 00:47:34.818
I had an alien implant. - Okay. hold on.

894
00:47:34.860 --> 00:47:36.300
I wanna unpack that.

895
00:47:51.120 --> 00:47:52.495
I asked them.

896
00:47:52.537 --> 00:47:56.007
"How many of these things
have you put in people?"

897
00:47:58.080 --> 00:48:00.078
The answer shocked me.

898
00:48:00.120 --> 00:48:04.077
They said. "Many thousands
over three generations now."

899
00:48:20.670 --> 00:48:22.698
Should I have my glasses on or off?

900
00:48:22.740 --> 00:48:25.038
Let's take
them off. if that's okay.

901
00:48:25.080 --> 00:48:27.528
So. Skyler and I. to some degree.

902
00:48:27.570 --> 00:48:30.438
are kind of like a mullet.
business in the front.

903
00:48:30.480 --> 00:48:31.638
she's party in the back.

904
00:48:31.680 --> 00:48:35.847
so we're just complimentary.
but very different (laughs).

905
00:48:36.750 --> 00:48:39.588
One day. we both woke
up and told each other

906
00:48:39.630 --> 00:48:41.268
that we both had this similar dream.

907
00:48:41.310 --> 00:48:45.318
And this first dream we
had was like this mansion

908
00:48:45.360 --> 00:48:46.518
that we were trapped in.

909
00:48:46.560 --> 00:48:48.828
Trapped in a house
or something like that.

910
00:48:48.870 --> 00:48:51.168
a scenario where we
were trying to escape and-

911
00:48:51.210 --> 00:48:53.778
And we both confirmed
that it was the same setup

912
00:48:53.820 --> 00:48:54.678
in this living room.

913
00:48:54.720 --> 00:48:56.208
The people that were in
the dream were the same.

914
00:48:56.250 --> 00:48:58.458
Probably a couple months after that.

915
00:48:58.500 --> 00:49:01.818
we both. again. had another dream

916
00:49:01.860 --> 00:49:03.108
and this one was completely-

917
00:49:03.150 --> 00:49:05.088
Different where we were at a family party

918
00:49:05.130 --> 00:49:07.578
and eventually all the kids in the dream-

919
00:49:07.620 --> 00:49:11.508
Were outside and there
was like a bouncy house

920
00:49:11.550 --> 00:49:13.398
that you would see like at a kid's party.

921
00:49:13.440 --> 00:49:17.058
but you could see there was
some sort of beings inside

922
00:49:17.100 --> 00:49:19.728
the bouncy house. but
they were not human beings.

923
00:49:19.770 --> 00:49:21.198
By the end of the dream.

924
00:49:21.240 --> 00:49:25.248
I remember kind of floating
or being like higher up.

925
00:49:25.290 --> 00:49:26.808
Floating tornado.

926
00:49:26.850 --> 00:49:29.028
Everything went black and
then we were thrown back down.

927
00:49:29.070 --> 00:49:30.648
And I remember there being a bluish.

928
00:49:30.690 --> 00:49:34.698
greenish hue throughout
the setting in my dream

929
00:49:34.740 --> 00:49:36.888
that I don't know why.

930
00:49:36.930 --> 00:49:38.808
but it just gave me the emotion

931
00:49:38.850 --> 00:49:42.352
of assuming it was something non-human.

932
00:49:46.350 --> 00:49:48.198
I have no idea what's gonna happen.

933
00:49:48.240 --> 00:49:50.658
I have no reference points.

934
00:49:50.700 --> 00:49:53.148
Skyler can't tell me anything.
won't tell me anything.

935
00:49:53.190 --> 00:49:55.383
so I have no idea what to expect.

936
00:49:57.510 --> 00:50:00.498
Best case scenario. we find
some interesting information

937
00:50:00.540 --> 00:50:04.578
that why maybe Skyler
and I both had these dreams

938
00:50:04.620 --> 00:50:06.258
on the same nights.

939
00:50:06.300 --> 00:50:09.648
Worst case. I am in the
same position as I am now.

940
00:50:09.690 --> 00:50:11.958
which is I know nothing more than me

941
00:50:12.000 --> 00:50:13.848
and Skyler had the same dream. same night.

942
00:50:13.890 --> 00:50:16.383
just really weird circumstances.

943
00:50:17.460 --> 00:50:19.668
So. what we'll do. I'll take you back.

944
00:50:19.710 --> 00:50:21.678
I'm gonna be regressing you back

945
00:50:21.720 --> 00:50:24.153
to when you were a little girl.

946
00:50:25.350 --> 00:50:30.258
Your subconscious may
remember. like I said. the exact age.

947
00:50:30.300 --> 00:50:32.628
I'm just nervous

948
00:50:32.670 --> 00:50:35.688
and a little anxious to
go through the process.

949
00:50:35.730 --> 00:50:38.343
but I'm excited to see
what comes out of it.

950
00:50:53.631 --> 00:50:57.745
It's very hard. it's
very hard to. you know.

951
00:50:57.787 --> 00:51:02.583
it's very tempting to just
sort of waffle about bullshit.

952
00:51:04.080 --> 00:51:07.843
but I think it's very hard to talk about it

953
00:51:07.885 --> 00:51:10.233
in a way that has any value.

954
00:51:13.950 --> 00:51:14.928
However. it's also very clear

955
00:51:14.970 --> 00:51:17.748
that the UFO phenomenon is multifaceted

956
00:51:17.790 --> 00:51:22.068
and far. far weirder than
most people have conceived of.

957
00:51:22.110 --> 00:51:24.828
I used to believe in a literal reality

958
00:51:24.870 --> 00:51:29.870
of gray beings visiting
us in technological craft

959
00:51:30.630 --> 00:51:32.388
and abducting people
and interacting with them

960
00:51:32.430 --> 00:51:34.188
for their own scientific agendas.

961
00:51:34.230 --> 00:51:36.528
And in a universe of
infinite possibilities.

962
00:51:36.570 --> 00:51:39.258
it has to be a possibility
and people do report it.

963
00:51:39.300 --> 00:51:44.300
But we have to question
the role of the experiencer

964
00:51:45.330 --> 00:51:47.148
in any of these alien encounters.

965
00:51:47.190 --> 00:51:49.878
In "Reframing the Debate."
the book that I edited.

966
00:51:49.920 --> 00:51:51.678
one of the authors. Greg Bishop.

967
00:51:51.720 --> 00:51:55.728
looks at this idea of co-creation.

968
00:51:55.770 --> 00:51:57.798
the idea that the UFO phenomenon

969
00:51:57.840 --> 00:51:59.298
and other paranormal phenomena

970
00:51:59.340 --> 00:52:02.718
are products of a co-creationalprocess

971
00:52:02.760 --> 00:52:04.518
between the observer and.

972
00:52:04.560 --> 00:52:07.098
yes. something that is separate from us.

973
00:52:07.140 --> 00:52:09.948
some exotic external stimuli.

974
00:52:09.990 --> 00:52:12.318
I think the biggest problem
with studying UFOs now

975
00:52:12.360 --> 00:52:16.188
is that people are
looking for that one cause.

976
00:52:16.230 --> 00:52:18.948
or they make an assumption about what it is

977
00:52:18.990 --> 00:52:23.178
and then they try to fit
their evidence that they find

978
00:52:23.220 --> 00:52:25.038
and the things that
they talk about to people

979
00:52:25.080 --> 00:52:27.108
and the things that they ask of witnesses

980
00:52:27.150 --> 00:52:29.508
to that preconception.

981
00:52:29.550 --> 00:52:31.608
whether it be they're
coming from other planets.

982
00:52:31.650 --> 00:52:35.868
which is basically 99.9%
of what people think

983
00:52:35.910 --> 00:52:37.488
when they're thinking about this.

984
00:52:37.530 --> 00:52:39.198
or they come from another dimension

985
00:52:39.240 --> 00:52:41.508
or another time or something like that.

986
00:52:41.550 --> 00:52:43.788
And if these beings do
actually turn out to be

987
00:52:43.830 --> 00:52:46.218
from the future. then ultimately.

988
00:52:46.260 --> 00:52:48.633
aren't we talking about
the human perspective?

989
00:52:50.250 --> 00:52:52.008
Some people have speculated

990
00:52:52.050 --> 00:52:55.428
that UFOs are a projection of us.

991
00:52:55.470 --> 00:52:57.768
I mean. Carl Young. of course. in the '50s.

992
00:52:57.810 --> 00:53:01.008
thought about the idea
that the UFO is symbolic

993
00:53:01.050 --> 00:53:04.518
of the human condition of
the wholeness of humanity

994
00:53:04.560 --> 00:53:06.528
and hence the UFO being circular.

995
00:53:06.570 --> 00:53:11.037
It's some kind of almost like
a metaphysical manifestation

996
00:53:11.079 --> 00:53:14.958
of our collective concerns.
anxieties. hopes. fears.

997
00:53:15.000 --> 00:53:19.248
desires about the universe at
this point in human evolution.

998
00:53:19.290 --> 00:53:22.578
So. that's a sort of
psychosocial theory for UFOs.

999
00:53:22.620 --> 00:53:24.708
But of course. how do you explain then

1000
00:53:24.750 --> 00:53:27.678
when a psychosocial phenomenon seems

1001
00:53:27.720 --> 00:53:31.608
to have physical effects
on witnesses on terra firma?

1002
00:53:31.650 --> 00:53:33.138
How do we account for this?

1003
00:53:33.180 --> 00:53:36.048
There seems to be an
ontological physical reality

1004
00:53:36.090 --> 00:53:36.881
to the phenomenon.

1005
00:53:36.923 --> 00:53:39.618
and so therefore people
automatically then go to the notion

1006
00:53:39.660 --> 00:53:41.118
that this must be extra terrestrial

1007
00:53:41.160 --> 00:53:42.378
because what else could that be?

1008
00:53:42.420 --> 00:53:43.638
When you look at it.

1009
00:53:43.680 --> 00:53:46.038
people react to it in
so many different ways.

1010
00:53:46.080 --> 00:53:50.148
I think it's something that
affects people very deeply

1011
00:53:50.190 --> 00:53:51.588
in some cases.

1012
00:53:51.630 --> 00:53:55.398
and that the variety that
we see in the UFO subject

1013
00:53:55.440 --> 00:53:59.598
is due mostly to the
variety we see in people

1014
00:53:59.640 --> 00:54:01.998
and how they perceive things
and how they remember things

1015
00:54:02.040 --> 00:54:03.438
and what their culture tells them.

1016
00:54:03.480 --> 00:54:05.013
It almost seems.

1017
00:54:06.240 --> 00:54:08.898
and this is a theory
that's been put forward

1018
00:54:08.940 --> 00:54:12.258
by Jacques Vallee and others.
that what we're witnessing.

1019
00:54:12.300 --> 00:54:14.898
what people are experiencing
is more of a performance.

1020
00:54:14.940 --> 00:54:18.678
it's theater on the part
of whatever intelligence

1021
00:54:18.720 --> 00:54:19.668
is involved here.

1022
00:54:19.710 --> 00:54:21.993
Like. why do UFOs have blinking lights?

1023
00:54:23.040 --> 00:54:23.831
What's that about?

1024
00:54:23.873 --> 00:54:25.008
They don't need blinking lights.

1025
00:54:25.050 --> 00:54:26.298
We don't need blinking lights on anything.

1026
00:54:26.340 --> 00:54:27.378
Why do they need blinking lights?

1027
00:54:27.420 --> 00:54:29.298
That's the show. that's for show.

1028
00:54:29.340 --> 00:54:31.338
The way they appear
to people in many cases.

1029
00:54:31.380 --> 00:54:32.418
especially in close encounters.

1030
00:54:32.460 --> 00:54:36.318
it seems like theater.
it seems over the top.

1031
00:54:36.360 --> 00:54:38.388
Obviously. what it is. it wants to be seen.

1032
00:54:38.430 --> 00:54:40.308
it wants us to be aware of it.

1033
00:54:40.350 --> 00:54:41.838
I suppose that's the one thing you can draw

1034
00:54:41.880 --> 00:54:42.828
from this quite certainly.

1035
00:54:42.870 --> 00:54:44.448
is that whatever the intelligence is.

1036
00:54:44.490 --> 00:54:46.818
it wants us to be aware of it.

1037
00:54:46.860 --> 00:54:50.568
Really. all we can do is to try to listen

1038
00:54:50.610 --> 00:54:52.728
to what witnesses have to say

1039
00:54:52.770 --> 00:54:57.770
without imposing any
pre-existing ideologies.

1040
00:54:58.140 --> 00:55:02.538
beliefs. expectations.
desires. obsessions onto that.

1041
00:55:02.580 --> 00:55:05.808
and just to try to gather
as much data as possible

1042
00:55:05.850 --> 00:55:07.728
and to put that data in the hands of people

1043
00:55:07.770 --> 00:55:11.058
who are qualified to make sense of it.

1044
00:55:11.100 --> 00:55:12.948
And in the UFO field. unfortunately.

1045
00:55:12.990 --> 00:55:14.058
there are very few people

1046
00:55:14.100 --> 00:55:17.058
who have any official formal qualifications

1047
00:55:17.100 --> 00:55:20.298
that would help us understand UFO data.

1048
00:55:20.340 --> 00:55:24.138
Basically. the UFO
phenomenon resides within us.

1049
00:55:24.180 --> 00:55:26.688
and I think if we concentrate on that.

1050
00:55:26.730 --> 00:55:27.978
things will start to change.

1051
00:55:28.020 --> 00:55:29.598
There will be an understanding.

1052
00:55:29.640 --> 00:55:31.518
not an answer. but an understanding.

1053
00:55:31.560 --> 00:55:33.318
I like the word understanding.

1054
00:55:33.360 --> 00:55:35.898
So. maybe that should be
part of the aim of ufology.

1055
00:55:35.940 --> 00:55:37.218
or people that study UFOs now.

1056
00:55:37.260 --> 00:55:39.258
is to understand what's going on.

1057
00:55:39.300 --> 00:55:42.393
not to come up with an
answer or to prove something.

1058
00:55:49.020 --> 00:55:50.748
Harvard professor or not.

1059
00:55:50.790 --> 00:55:55.368
anyone who believes what
you do would believe anything.

1060
00:55:55.410 --> 00:55:56.201
Yeah. I mean.

1061
00:55:56.243 --> 00:55:58.128
it's really not a matter
of believing. Richard.

1062
00:55:58.170 --> 00:56:00.918
I mean. I think to me.

1063
00:56:00.960 --> 00:56:02.598
this was utterly not possible

1064
00:56:02.640 --> 00:56:06.198
when I first heard about it
and I didn't write about it.

1065
00:56:06.240 --> 00:56:09.228
I didn't speak publicly
about it for two years.

1066
00:56:09.270 --> 00:56:11.410
This grew out of the experiences

1067
00:56:12.360 --> 00:56:14.148
of case after case after case.

1068
00:56:14.190 --> 00:56:16.293
So. it was not like believing anything.

1069
00:56:17.250 --> 00:56:20.178
I came cautiously. reluctantly.

1070
00:56:20.220 --> 00:56:24.455
gradually to take this
as seriously as I did.

1071
00:56:40.350 --> 00:56:43.383
I am maybe better known as Kathie Davis

1072
00:56:43.425 --> 00:56:45.528
in Budd Hopkins' book. "Intruders."

1073
00:56:45.570 --> 00:56:49.068
I had experiences most of my life

1074
00:56:49.110 --> 00:56:53.748
and a big experience in June 30th. 1983.

1075
00:56:53.790 --> 00:56:55.638
Prior to finding out I was pregnant.

1076
00:56:55.680 --> 00:56:56.558
I was out with my friend

1077
00:56:56.600 --> 00:56:59.238
in the middle of the
night stalking her boyfriend

1078
00:56:59.280 --> 00:57:00.528
in the corn fields

1079
00:57:00.570 --> 00:57:04.908
and we had this weird
encounter with this crazy light.

1080
00:57:04.950 --> 00:57:09.950
It was funny because she
remembered more of the incident

1081
00:57:10.290 --> 00:57:11.118
than I did.

1082
00:57:11.160 --> 00:57:12.168
You mean the light on the ground?

1083
00:57:12.210 --> 00:57:13.578
And I'm like. "What light on the ground?"

1084
00:57:13.620 --> 00:57:15.648
She actually remembered the
light coming down on the ground.

1085
00:57:15.690 --> 00:57:18.333
I remembered being pulled
out of the car by my legs.

1086
00:57:22.140 --> 00:57:25.728
After that experience. I
found out that I was pregnant.

1087
00:57:25.770 --> 00:57:28.128
My pregnancy was confirmed by our doctor.

1088
00:57:28.170 --> 00:57:31.338
and he actually thought I
might be a little farther along

1089
00:57:31.380 --> 00:57:32.358
than I thought I was.

1090
00:57:32.400 --> 00:57:34.090
I was already engaged

1091
00:57:35.220 --> 00:57:37.548
and we already had a
wedding date set for June.

1092
00:57:37.590 --> 00:57:39.078
but we went ahead and moved it up to April

1093
00:57:39.120 --> 00:57:40.698
so I wouldn't be giant pregnant.

1094
00:57:40.740 --> 00:57:44.328
About 3 1/2 to four months into it.

1095
00:57:44.370 --> 00:57:45.828
I had another strange experience

1096
00:57:45.870 --> 00:57:50.103
while babysitting for my sister
and I woke up the next day.

1097
00:57:51.030 --> 00:57:53.778
immediately thinking something
was wrong with my baby.

1098
00:57:53.820 --> 00:57:57.858
I ended up going to a
facility with a friend of mine

1099
00:57:57.900 --> 00:58:00.828
and had another pregnancy
test. which came back negative.

1100
00:58:00.870 --> 00:58:05.478
The doctor never explained
to me where my baby went.

1101
00:58:05.520 --> 00:58:07.488
why my pregnancy was suddenly not there.

1102
00:58:07.530 --> 00:58:09.588
He just said he'd seen it before

1103
00:58:09.630 --> 00:58:12.708
and that it would be
best that I'd just forget

1104
00:58:12.750 --> 00:58:16.158
that this ever happened and
I would get pregnant again.

1105
00:58:16.200 --> 00:58:17.448
I was young and I'd have other kids

1106
00:58:17.490 --> 00:58:19.233
and I shouldn't worry about it.

1107
00:58:20.160 --> 00:58:22.848
But I knew when I woke up the next morning

1108
00:58:22.890 --> 00:58:25.248
and thought there's something
wrong. where's my baby?

1109
00:58:25.290 --> 00:58:27.948
And then before I went
to Planned Parenthood.

1110
00:58:27.990 --> 00:58:30.978
I knew the baby was a
girl and I don't know how.

1111
00:58:31.020 --> 00:58:34.428
but I knew that it was a girl.

1112
00:58:34.470 --> 00:58:36.738
To say this. it was like really hard

1113
00:58:36.780 --> 00:58:39.348
because you're trying to talk
about people being abducted

1114
00:58:39.390 --> 00:58:41.838
and they go. "Oh yeah.
now they're. you know?"

1115
00:58:41.880 --> 00:58:45.768
And I said it one time
on a talk show in the '90s.

1116
00:58:45.810 --> 00:58:47.217
and oh my God (laughs).

1117
00:58:48.300 --> 00:58:51.018
You just opened up a can of worms

1118
00:58:51.060 --> 00:58:52.548
and then you gotta explain that.

1119
00:58:52.590 --> 00:58:54.565
And I'm always asked.

1120
00:58:54.607 --> 00:58:57.408
"Why are these alien beings doing this?

1121
00:58:57.450 --> 00:59:00.198
Why are they abducting people?"

1122
00:59:00.240 --> 00:59:02.898
And from all the years
of research that I've done.

1123
00:59:02.940 --> 00:59:07.940
I feel very strongly that there
is a cross-breeding program

1124
00:59:09.390 --> 00:59:13.173
with alien beings and humans.

1125
00:59:15.150 --> 00:59:18.168
I was on a table and
I remember looking up

1126
00:59:18.210 --> 00:59:21.288
and seeing two of them walking in with her.

1127
00:59:21.330 --> 00:59:22.863
holding her hands.

1128
00:59:23.880 --> 00:59:25.908
And when she came into the room.

1129
00:59:25.950 --> 00:59:29.680
she looked at me and then she looked away

1130
00:59:30.540 --> 00:59:32.553
and she was afraid of me.

1131
00:59:34.164 --> 00:59:36.318
And I immediately felt sad.

1132
00:59:36.360 --> 00:59:37.668
When I looked at this baby. I'm like.

1133
00:59:37.710 --> 00:59:41.598
"This is my baby. this is my daughter."

1134
00:59:41.640 --> 00:59:44.268
And then when she looked at me

1135
00:59:44.310 --> 00:59:46.098
and she looked like she was scared of me.

1136
00:59:46.140 --> 00:59:47.838
it hurt my feelings.

1137
00:59:47.880 --> 00:59:48.671
And then I thought.

1138
00:59:48.713 --> 00:59:51.828
"Well. it's like she never seen anybody

1139
00:59:51.870 --> 00:59:53.118
who looked like me before."

1140
00:59:53.160 --> 00:59:55.578
And I might have looked
scary to her. I guess.

1141
00:59:55.620 --> 00:59:56.411
Do you know.

1142
00:59:56.453 --> 01:00:00.257
do you have any idea why
they presented her to you?

1143
01:00:00.299 --> 01:00:01.564
No. I do not.

1144
01:00:01.606 --> 01:00:03.202
Did you get
to touch her or hold her at all?

1145
01:00:03.244 --> 01:00:04.077
No.

1146
01:00:06.492 --> 01:00:07.325
No.

1147
01:00:10.530 --> 01:00:12.018
The question might be. why?

1148
01:00:12.060 --> 01:00:13.398
Why would they be doing this?

1149
01:00:13.440 --> 01:00:16.098
If I was the alien
coming back through time.

1150
01:00:16.140 --> 01:00:18.738
why would I be taking
this genetic material?

1151
01:00:18.780 --> 01:00:21.108
And in looking at past and current trends.

1152
01:00:21.150 --> 01:00:25.308
500 years ago. we had very
isolated. separate groups.

1153
01:00:25.350 --> 01:00:27.288
inner breeding populations. that.

1154
01:00:27.330 --> 01:00:29.868
beginning primarily with
European colonialism.

1155
01:00:29.910 --> 01:00:31.248
started to amalgamate.

1156
01:00:31.290 --> 01:00:35.028
We started to get homogenization
of our genetic material.

1157
01:00:35.070 --> 01:00:37.818
If that trend continued into the future.

1158
01:00:37.860 --> 01:00:41.208
we might expect problems
similar to those we have today

1159
01:00:41.250 --> 01:00:42.843
with highly inbred groups.

1160
01:00:46.560 --> 01:00:47.868
To get around those problems.

1161
01:00:47.910 --> 01:00:50.838
one of the only places you
could find new gene variants

1162
01:00:50.880 --> 01:00:53.418
would be to sample haplo groups

1163
01:00:53.460 --> 01:00:55.518
that never made it into the future.

1164
01:00:55.560 --> 01:00:59.028
Those would offer you
the ability to find new genes

1165
01:00:59.070 --> 01:01:02.148
to put into an overly
homogenized population

1166
01:01:02.190 --> 01:01:04.188
to alleviate some of these problems.

1167
01:01:04.230 --> 01:01:05.298
We do this today.

1168
01:01:05.340 --> 01:01:07.338
it's a very important strategy used

1169
01:01:07.380 --> 01:01:08.868
in conservation measures.

1170
01:01:08.910 --> 01:01:10.878
When we have a small isolated group

1171
01:01:10.920 --> 01:01:13.548
where gene drift takes
over and causes problems.

1172
01:01:13.590 --> 01:01:17.178
we look for the most
different genotypes available

1173
01:01:17.220 --> 01:01:19.068
to hybridize with these groups

1174
01:01:19.110 --> 01:01:21.183
in order to overcome these problems.

1175
01:01:24.150 --> 01:01:26.088
I think we're very far from consensus

1176
01:01:26.130 --> 01:01:28.428
that range from people
who just think that there's

1177
01:01:28.470 --> 01:01:30.588
so little data it's not
even worth talking about

1178
01:01:30.630 --> 01:01:32.958
to people who. some scientists.

1179
01:01:33.000 --> 01:01:35.298
colleagues of mine who have materials

1180
01:01:35.340 --> 01:01:39.018
that are supposedly from
ships that seem hard to explain.

1181
01:01:39.060 --> 01:01:42.393
In my laboratory. we
ban the word impossible.

1182
01:01:44.250 --> 01:01:49.250
Even some physics limits get
questioned from time to time.

1183
01:01:51.810 --> 01:01:53.508
So. I think it's possible.

1184
01:01:53.550 --> 01:01:56.583
We don't have enough evidence to doubt it.

1185
01:01:58.126 --> 01:02:00.318
and so that's another reason why. you know.

1186
01:02:00.360 --> 01:02:04.308
68% of citizens have an open mind

1187
01:02:04.350 --> 01:02:06.018
to both the existence of aliens

1188
01:02:06.060 --> 01:02:07.460
and the government cover up.

1189
01:02:10.620 --> 01:02:13.338
So. Deb. I have to ask you.

1190
01:02:13.380 --> 01:02:15.138
and I'm sure you've gotten this before.

1191
01:02:15.180 --> 01:02:18.378
but as compelling as your story is.

1192
01:02:18.420 --> 01:02:22.218
and I'm as a former
assistant attorney general.

1193
01:02:22.260 --> 01:02:23.418
you can appreciate it.

1194
01:02:23.460 --> 01:02:27.198
There's just no evidence
that this ever took place

1195
01:02:27.240 --> 01:02:31.779
in the physical world. so
how do you answer to that?

1196
01:02:37.230 --> 01:02:42.230
I'm not sure where they
come from or how they get here.

1197
01:02:42.330 --> 01:02:43.788
but I've had experiences

1198
01:02:43.830 --> 01:02:46.983
that actually left
physical marks in the yard.

1199
01:02:49.950 --> 01:02:52.563
So. that's a physical level to it.

1200
01:02:54.180 --> 01:02:58.758
And also I've developed
this sort of like sixth sense

1201
01:02:58.800 --> 01:02:59.898
as I've gotten older

1202
01:02:59.940 --> 01:03:02.718
and this ability to kind of feel people

1203
01:03:02.760 --> 01:03:04.698
in their thoughts and stuff.

1204
01:03:04.740 --> 01:03:07.158
sometimes just as I walk by them.

1205
01:03:07.200 --> 01:03:08.448
and I don't even do it on purpose

1206
01:03:08.490 --> 01:03:11.358
and I often wonder if that's a side effect

1207
01:03:11.400 --> 01:03:14.148
of this communication that was between me

1208
01:03:14.190 --> 01:03:17.688
and these entities or these things.

1209
01:03:17.730 --> 01:03:20.148
In 2012. I woke up in the morning

1210
01:03:20.190 --> 01:03:25.068
and threw my legs over the
bed and stood up and I fell.

1211
01:03:25.110 --> 01:03:26.988
I couldn't support weight on my right leg.

1212
01:03:27.030 --> 01:03:28.608
They took me into the x-ray room

1213
01:03:28.650 --> 01:03:30.588
and they did a couple x-rays

1214
01:03:30.630 --> 01:03:34.368
and the woman seemed kind
of perplexed and she asked me.

1215
01:03:34.410 --> 01:03:37.008
she said. "Have you had a
shrapnel wound or something

1216
01:03:37.050 --> 01:03:39.468
to account for a piece
of metal in your leg?"

1217
01:03:39.510 --> 01:03:41.808
And I explained. "No.
I'd never had any injury

1218
01:03:41.850 --> 01:03:43.338
to that leg whatsoever."

1219
01:03:43.380 --> 01:03:44.171
And then she said.

1220
01:03:44.213 --> 01:03:47.238
"I'm gonna ask a radiologist
to come down and take a look."

1221
01:03:47.280 --> 01:03:49.248
He put this film up.

1222
01:03:49.290 --> 01:03:53.538
He said. "You have here what
appears to be bones arranged"

1223
01:03:53.580 --> 01:03:56.478
in a floret pattern in the
calf muscle of your leg.

1224
01:03:56.520 --> 01:03:59.538
And I ask. "Is that unusual. doctor?"

1225
01:03:59.580 --> 01:04:02.328
And he says. "Well. bone
does not typically sprout

1226
01:04:02.370 --> 01:04:03.948
in the middle of muscle tissue."

1227
01:04:03.990 --> 01:04:05.808
And he was talking to the technician

1228
01:04:05.850 --> 01:04:07.938
and for her benefit. I think.

1229
01:04:07.980 --> 01:04:10.248
he walked over to me
and poked me in the leg

1230
01:04:10.290 --> 01:04:13.398
and said to her. "It'll be right here."

1231
01:04:13.440 --> 01:04:16.308
And I interrupted and I said.
"What will be right there?"

1232
01:04:16.350 --> 01:04:17.141
And he told me. he says.

1233
01:04:17.183 --> 01:04:19.008
"Well. you have to have a scar there."

1234
01:04:19.050 --> 01:04:22.210
He says. "Anytime you
break the integrity of the skin"

1235
01:04:23.070 --> 01:04:25.968
to have an object like
this buried into the fascia

1236
01:04:26.010 --> 01:04:30.048
"and the tissue that deep.
that's gonna leave a scar."

1237
01:04:30.090 --> 01:04:31.758
And he asked his intern to run up

1238
01:04:31.800 --> 01:04:36.108
and get a handheld black
light. which she brought back.

1239
01:04:36.150 --> 01:04:38.208
And he says. "Scar
tissue will fluoresce under

1240
01:04:38.250 --> 01:04:40.008
a black light. we'll find it."

1241
01:04:40.050 --> 01:04:41.028
He turned off the lights

1242
01:04:41.070 --> 01:04:42.978
and he examined my knee again

1243
01:04:43.020 --> 01:04:47.778
and he was obviously
confused. frustrated. confounded.

1244
01:04:47.820 --> 01:04:48.805
And I asked him. I said.

1245
01:04:48.847 --> 01:04:51.228
"Doctor. how often is it that you find

1246
01:04:51.270 --> 01:04:53.988
a foreign object buried
into the skin at this depth.

1247
01:04:54.030 --> 01:04:57.258
at this size without there
being a corresponding scar?"

1248
01:04:57.300 --> 01:05:00.387
And he thought for a
second and said. "Never."

1249
01:05:01.279 --> 01:05:03.468
He said. "I've been a
radiologist for 23 years.

1250
01:05:03.510 --> 01:05:05.127
I've never seen this before."

1251
01:05:07.860 --> 01:05:12.228
November 16th. 2017. I
woke up in the morning

1252
01:05:12.270 --> 01:05:14.478
with a lot of pain in my upper legs.

1253
01:05:14.520 --> 01:05:16.825
Somehow I knew. I told my wife. I said.

1254
01:05:16.867 --> 01:05:18.408
"They came last night

1255
01:05:18.450 --> 01:05:20.028
and they took this thing outta my leg."

1256
01:05:20.070 --> 01:05:21.708
and she says. "Well.
you gotta get an x-ray."

1257
01:05:21.750 --> 01:05:24.295
So. I made my way to a
chiropractic office and I said.

1258
01:05:24.337 --> 01:05:25.638
"Well. doctor. real quick.

1259
01:05:25.680 --> 01:05:27.288
I need an x-ray of my right leg

1260
01:05:27.330 --> 01:05:30.225
because I had an alien implant from 1977

1261
01:05:30.267 --> 01:05:32.928
and I think aliens came
last night and took it out."

1262
01:05:32.970 --> 01:05:34.428
And he's got me by the arm

1263
01:05:34.470 --> 01:05:36.708
and he's leading me to the front door.

1264
01:05:36.750 --> 01:05:38.178
And I know chiropractors look

1265
01:05:38.220 --> 01:05:40.368
at maybe a hundred x-rays a week.

1266
01:05:40.410 --> 01:05:44.028
and I'm holding my x-rays
up in front of his face

1267
01:05:44.070 --> 01:05:48.597
and he stops dead in his tracks
and he says. "Come with me."

1268
