01:19:32.130 --> 01:19:32.928
when I watched my.

1517
01:19:32.970 --> 01:19:34.728
it was like I was watching myself

1518
01:19:34.770 --> 01:19:36.618
and I was like checking on myself.

1519
01:19:36.660 --> 01:19:40.128
But then I looked at my closet

1520
01:19:40.170 --> 01:19:43.938
and there was this tall amoeba shape. tall.

1521
01:19:43.980 --> 01:19:45.783
It wasn't. like. nothing was even about it.

1522
01:19:45.825 --> 01:19:46.968
It looked like an amoeba.

1523
01:19:47.010 --> 01:19:48.588
It was tall and it was just there.

1524
01:19:48.630 --> 01:19:51.858
I found it interesting
that we both saw figures.

1525
01:19:51.900 --> 01:19:56.253
but they were both
different types of forms.

1526
01:19:59.820 --> 01:20:01.818
I also thought one of
the most interesting things

1527
01:20:01.860 --> 01:20:06.860
of her hypnosis session was
that she saw the dark glass.

1528
01:20:07.800 --> 01:20:09.948
like the two-way mirror glass kind of thing

1529
01:20:09.990 --> 01:20:11.988
that she felt like people could see in.

1530
01:20:12.030 --> 01:20:13.608
but she couldn't see out.

1531
01:20:13.650 --> 01:20:17.088
and that's kind of exactly
how I felt about the eyes I saw.

1532
01:20:17.130 --> 01:20:18.678
So. I found that very interesting

1533
01:20:18.720 --> 01:20:21.888
and I wonder if maybe
that's somehow connected.

1534
01:20:21.930 --> 01:20:24.405
Weird that you had the
same experience with my room

1535
01:20:24.447 --> 01:20:26.023
and I can't believe that you were in pain.

1536
01:20:26.065 --> 01:20:26.898
I'm sorry.

1537
01:20:27.960 --> 01:20:29.765
I'm glad that we're okay and I love you.

1538
01:20:29.807 --> 01:20:30.873
I love you too.

1539
01:20:35.850 --> 01:20:39.357
It's crazy. I'm
so happy you came out.

1540
01:20:43.870 --> 01:20:45.558
I have no idea how
the abductees are chosen.

1541
01:20:45.600 --> 01:20:49.728
They seem to cut across
every socioeconomic level.

1542
01:20:49.770 --> 01:20:52.908
They seem to be unusually mentally sound.

1543
01:20:52.950 --> 01:20:54.258
In other words. they seem to pick people

1544
01:20:54.300 --> 01:20:58.653
who are particularly
strong. stable. open-minded.

1545
01:21:00.150 --> 01:21:03.378
There's something profoundly
important going on here

1546
01:21:03.420 --> 01:21:05.643
that is authentic and real.

1547
01:21:08.610 --> 01:21:12.138
I think that we might
use this reflection on aliens

1548
01:21:12.180 --> 01:21:14.328
as an opportunity to think about our future

1549
01:21:14.370 --> 01:21:17.598
or using what we know
about how quickly we're going

1550
01:21:17.640 --> 01:21:21.228
to project on how quickly
other species might go.

1551
01:21:21.270 --> 01:21:23.388
so we're prepared for
ourselves in the future

1552
01:21:23.430 --> 01:21:26.808
so that we could become
one of those creatures

1553
01:21:26.850 --> 01:21:30.168
and we might visit ourselves in some way.

1554
01:21:30.210 --> 01:21:32.298
We go off the planet and come back.

1555
01:21:32.340 --> 01:21:37.340
or we just become that staying in place.

1556
01:21:37.440 --> 01:21:38.928
and that we need to think about

1557
01:21:38.970 --> 01:21:41.478
the possible alternative
ways of being human.

1558
01:21:41.520 --> 01:21:42.528
But if they are out there.

1559
01:21:42.570 --> 01:21:47.570
it would change maybe
my priorities and worldview.

1560
01:21:47.730 --> 01:21:49.188
So. the sooner the better.

1561
01:21:49.230 --> 01:21:50.268
If they don't exist.

1562
01:21:50.310 --> 01:21:53.058
it will not necessarily be
intensely disappointing.

1563
01:21:53.100 --> 01:21:55.998
but I think we then have a huge.

1564
01:21:56.040 --> 01:21:59.058
even bigger obligation to spread ourselves

1565
01:21:59.100 --> 01:22:00.168
through the galaxy

1566
01:22:00.210 --> 01:22:03.438
if we're the only intelligent
life form in the universe.

1567
01:22:03.480 --> 01:22:06.195
it seems like it's a pretty cool thing

1568
01:22:06.237 --> 01:22:08.463
and you wouldn't want
it to be extinguished.

1569
01:22:24.840 --> 01:22:27.678
I was walking into something.

1570
01:22:27.720 --> 01:22:30.378
not realizing I was
actually walking a plank.

1571
01:22:30.420 --> 01:22:31.818
Let me put it that way.

1572
01:22:31.860 --> 01:22:34.518
The book was published
and I fell off the plank

1573
01:22:34.560 --> 01:22:37.908
and ended up underwater. basically.

1574
01:22:37.950 --> 01:22:39.750
That's what happened to me publicly.

1575
01:22:42.600 --> 01:22:45.948
People who do what I do as a comedian

1576
01:22:45.990 --> 01:22:49.908
have had a huge impact to
make the subject seem ridiculous.

1577
01:22:49.950 --> 01:22:52.998
And I regret it 'cause I
think I was insensitive

1578
01:22:53.040 --> 01:22:53.958
to some people I knew.

1579
01:22:54.000 --> 01:22:56.778
I think it's great that
experiencers can come out

1580
01:22:56.820 --> 01:23:01.218
and talk about their
experiences. their abductions.

1581
01:23:01.260 --> 01:23:03.768
their encounters with aliens.

1582
01:23:03.810 --> 01:23:06.318
I think they should be
accepted. not ridiculed.

1583
01:23:06.360 --> 01:23:09.258
and people will ridicule
them because we're human.

1584
01:23:09.300 --> 01:23:12.393
I find them compelling
and I find them believable.

1585
01:23:19.770 --> 01:23:22.488
And one of the motivations
for me in reporting on this

1586
01:23:22.530 --> 01:23:27.168
is the passion I feel
about the individual people

1587
01:23:27.210 --> 01:23:30.078
who are involved with this
who aren't taken seriously.

1588
01:23:30.120 --> 01:23:33.348
Experiencers report getting
messages telepathically

1589
01:23:33.390 --> 01:23:35.778
about taking care of our planet better.

1590
01:23:35.820 --> 01:23:38.868
If there's any kind of a
purpose in there being here.

1591
01:23:38.910 --> 01:23:40.668
that might affect our planet.

1592
01:23:40.710 --> 01:23:42.468
and this could be part of the power

1593
01:23:42.510 --> 01:23:45.288
that the whole question
of UFOs carries for people.

1594
01:23:45.330 --> 01:23:48.978
So many abductive tell me.
"I don't want them to leave.

1595
01:23:49.020 --> 01:23:50.628
I don't want this to stop

1596
01:23:50.670 --> 01:23:53.118
because I wanna know
why they've been doing this.

1597
01:23:53.160 --> 01:23:56.538
I wanna know why they
chose me and my family."

1598
01:23:56.580 --> 01:23:59.688
And I am hoping myself
that they don't just stop.

1599
01:23:59.730 --> 01:24:01.428
because I want answers too.

1600
01:24:01.470 --> 01:24:04.068
But in my experience in doing my work.

1601
01:24:04.110 --> 01:24:06.183
I doubt if they're just gonna stop.
